parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, and strand the driver.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
often while driving
and may not restart immediately. The check engine light may come on
and the vehicle may vibrate or shake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failures can cause the vehicle to stall, catch fire, or become stranded, leading to accidents and safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience intermittent starting issues
dim or missing instrument panel lights
and faulty brake lights. The battery may drain overnight
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake system failures can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake lights may remain illuminated while driving
and the vehicle may experience hard shifting or vibrations when braking. The brake pedal may feel soft or spongy
and the vehicle may pull to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The water ingress and corrosion can cause electrical system failures, engine damage, and safety risks.

causing corrosion and damage to electrical components. The vehicle may experience faulty instrument panel lights
and the touchscreen may malfunction.
